methods.name: GetCustomBuildNanite
methods.doc: Get whether the static mesh factory should set the Nanite build setting. Return false if the attribute was not set.

methods.name: GetCustomBuildReversedIndexBuffer
methods.doc: Get whether the static mesh should build a reversed index buffer.

methods.name: GetCustomBuildScale3D
methods.doc: Get the local scale that is applied when building the static mesh.

methods.name: GetCustomDistanceFieldReplacementMesh
methods.doc: Get the static mesh asset whose distance field will be used as the distance field for the imported mesh.

methods.name: GetCustomDistanceFieldResolutionScale
methods.doc:
Get the scale to apply to the mesh when allocating the distance field volume texture.
The default scale is 1, which assumes that the mesh will be placed unscaled in the world.

methods.name: GetCustomDstLightmapIndex
methods.doc: Get the index of the UV that is used to store generated lightmaps for the static mesh.

methods.name: GetCustomGenerateDistanceFieldAsIfTwoSided
methods.doc:
Get whether to generate the distance field by treating every triangle hit as a front face.
This prevents the distance field from being discarded due to the mesh being open, but also lowers distance field ambient occlusion quality.

methods.name: GetCustomGenerateLightmapUVs
methods.doc: Get whether the static mesh should generate lightmap UVs.

methods.name: GetCustomMaxLumenMeshCards
methods.doc:
Get the maximum number of Lumen mesh cards to generate for this mesh.
More cards means that the surface will have better coverage, but will result in increased runtime overhead.
Set this to 0 to disable mesh card generation for this mesh.
The default is 12.

methods.name: GetCustomMinLightmapResolution
methods.doc: Get the amount of padding used to pack UVs for the static mesh.

methods.name: GetCustomSrcLightmapIndex
methods.doc: Get the index of the UV that is used as the source for generating lightmaps for the static mesh.

methods.name: GetCustomSupportFaceRemap
methods.doc: Get whether the static mesh is set up for use with physical material masks.

methods.name: GetObjectClass
methods.doc: Get the class this node creates.

methods.name: GetSocketUidCount
methods.doc: Return the number of socket UIDs this static mesh has.
